  "prompt": "How do I log in my Facebook account if you forgot your password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Facebook password, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook Login Page**: Open a web browser and go to the Facebook website (www.facebook.com).\n\n2. **Click on 'Forgotten Password?'**: Below the password field, you should see a link labeled \"Forgotten password?\" Click on it.\n\n3. **Enter Your Information**: You will be prompted to enter your email address or phone number associated with your Facebook account. Enter the required information.\n\n4. **Identify Your Account**: Once you input your information, click on \"Search\" to find your account. If your account is found, it will display your profile picture and name.\n\n5. **Choose a Reset Method**: Facebook will offer options to send a code to your registered email address or phone number. Choose your preferred method and click \"Continue.\"\n\n6. **Enter the Code**: Check your email or text messages for the code Facebook sent you. Enter this code in the field provided on the Facebook page and click \"Continue.\"\n\n7. **Create a New Password**: Once you've entered the correct code, you will be prompted to enter a new password. Make sure to choose a strong, unique password that you haven't used before.\n\n8. **Log In**: After you set your new password, you should be able to log in to Facebook with it.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, ensure that you have access to the email account or phone number you are trying to use. If you don't have access, follow the on-screen instructions for further assistance. For additional help, you can also visit Facebook's Help Center.",
